{"key":"post-16328347","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16328347</id>\n<content>The brown gypsum is generally regular powder gypsum with a binding agent so it can be applied on farms with mechanical equipment.&amp;nbsp; The pellet gypsum will go through machinery where the powder gypsum would clog it up.&amp;nbsp; It's fine to use if you're not certified organic.&amp;nbsp; We can't use it on our mushroom substrates because the binding agent is a prohibited substance under USDA regs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you use it, simply mix it in with your bulk substrate before adding water.&amp;nbsp; Don't tear up your coffee grinder trying to grind it up.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16328374</next>\n<prev>16328001</prev>\n<first>16327739</first>\n<last>16328429</last>\n<when>1338777150</when>\n<utime>06/04/12 05:32 AM</utime>\n</post>"}